               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18400615-name-1325" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18400615-name-1325" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400615-name-1325" type="surname" value="WHITTAKER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400615-name-1325" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>HENRY WHITTAKER</persName>
                  </hi>. I live in Manor-street, Clapham. In the after<lb></lb> noon of the 19th of May, I was in Gravel-lane, Southwark, about half-past three o'clock—there was a fire—some persons were standing there, but I was passing on my business—I felt some one at my pocket—I turned, and saw the prisoner in the act of dropping my handkerchief from his hand—he was close to my back—I took him into custody—he said it was not him, but I saw him drop it—this is my handkerchief which is now produced.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner</hi>. I said I was not the person—and there were persons there who said, " You have got your property, let him go." <hi rend="italic">Witness</hi>. There were three women who said it was not him, and those women followed him down to the office each day he went there.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence</hi>. I am innocent. I made application to respectable persons in the crowd, who said I was not the person.</p>
